docs.snippet: The dollar was irregularly higher last week, measured by the quotation for the French franc. It had a strong start, at 64.44 cents on Monday, and held around the 64-cent level until Saturday, when it slumped to 63.60, closing at 63.76, which was a...
docs.lead_paragraph: The dollar was irregularly higher last week, measured by the quotation for the French franc. It had a strong start, at 64.44 cents on Monday, and held around the 64-cent level until Saturday, when it slumped to 63.60, closing at 63.76, which was a net gain over the previous week of .14. Range a year ago was 100.39@100.23 cents.

docs.snippet: BUENOS AIRES, Jan. 16. -- Argentina's efforts to arrange a Chaco peace ended in failure today. The Foreign Office presented a memorandum of its effort to the League of Nations Chaco commission and terminated its mediation without giving out details.

docs.lead_paragraph: KEY WEST, Fla., Jan. 19. -- Jefferson Caffery, President Roosevelt's personal representative in Cuba, is much encouraged with conditions existing in Cuba and believes that President Carlos Mendieta will shortly have the island republic back to normal.

docs.snippet: WASHINGTON, Jan. 19. -- Recognition of Cuba by the United States became a distinct possibility today as tentative plans were made known involving the opening of action looking toward recognition within a week or ten days.
